					<msContents class="lccn.loc.gov/n79090052" rend="visible">
						<summary>A service book, according to the Yemenite rite.</summary>
						<textLang mainLang="he" otherLangs="jrb"> </textLang>
						<msItem n="0" rend="visible" class="lccn.loc.gov/n79090052">
							<locus from="1r" to="213v"/>
							<title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Sidur</title>
							<title xml:lang="he">סדור</title>
							<note>
								<p>The text is provided with the superlinear punctuation, with the exceptions of the book of Lamentations and the biblical verse at the head of the services, which have the ordinary punctuation.</p>
								<p>References are found in the margin to e.g. Shulḥan Arukh, David ibn Abudraham, Sharira, Natronai, Sar Shalom, Radaḳ, Amram Gaon. There are explanations of a number of difficult words in Arabic. In some cases the reading of the text is marked as 'ha-nusḥah ha-nekhonah' or 'ha-nuskḥah ha-meduyeḳet' (folio 99r, 150v, 157v).</p>
							</note>
						</msItem>
						<msItem rend="">
							<locus from="1v" to="12r"/>
							<title xml:lang="en">Services for week-days</title>
						</msItem>
						<msItem rend="">
							<locus from="12r" to="24r"/>
							<title xml:lang="en">Services for Sabbath</title>
							<note>
								<p>Includes reading from Is. 56:8, 58:13-14; Jer. 17:21-22; Ex. 16:29.</p>
							</note>
						</msItem>
						<msItem rend="">
							<locus from="24r" to="25v"/>
							<title xml:lang="en">Services for Rosh ḥodesh</title>
						</msItem>
						<msItem rend="">
							<locus from="25v" to="34v"/>
							<title xml:lang="en">Services for Pesaḥ</title>
							<note>
								<p>No mention of halel at the end of tefilat lele Pesaḥim.</p>
							</note>
						</msItem>
						<msItem rend="">
							<locus from="34v" to="35v"/>
							<title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Tefilat ḥag ha-Shavu῾ot</title>
						</msItem>
						<msItem rend="">
							<locus from="35v" to="36r"/>
