						</msItem>
						<msItem rend="">
							<locus from="159r" to="191r"/>
							<title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Shirot ṿe-tishbahot</title>
						</msItem>
						<msItem rend="">
							<locus from="191r" to="195r"/>
							<title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Masekhet yoma</title>
							<note>
								<p>The text ends with the piyuṭ Shofeṭ kol ha-arets.</p>
							</note>
						</msItem>
						<msItem rend="">
							<locus from="195r" to="213v"/>
							<title xml:lang="en">Additions</title>
						</msItem>
					</msContents>
					<physDesc rend="visible">
						<p>Paper codex of the 17th century.</p>
						<objectDesc form="codex">
							<supportDesc material="chart">
								<support>Paper</support>
								<extent>213 folios <dimensions unit="mm" type="leaf">
										<height>280</height>
										<width>200</width>
									</dimensions>
									<dimensions type="written" unit="mm">
										<height>225</height>
										<width>140</width>
									</dimensions>
								</extent>
								<foliation>
									<p>213 folios (+ 2 unfoliated paper flyleaves at the beginning and at the end).</p>
								</foliation>
								<collation>
									<p>Quires of originally 10 leaves each, marked by catchwords at the end (mostly not preserved).</p>
								</collation>
								<condition>
									<p>Leaves stuck on paper (modern restoration).</p>
									<p>Folios damaged at the beginning and at the end.</p>
									<p>Only about half of folio 212 preserved.</p>
								</condition>
							</supportDesc>
							<layoutDesc>
								<layout columns="1 " ruledLines="30" writtenLines="30">
									<p>Uniform layout. </p>
									<p>Visible mastara ruling.</p>
									<p>Initial words written in larger characters.</p>
									<p>Leaf catchwords on every verso.</p>
									<p>Numerous marginal notes and additions.</p>
								</layout>
							</layoutDesc>
						</objectDesc>
						<handDesc hands="2">
							<summary>Yemenite semi-cursive script, punctuated, of the 17th century.</summary>
							<handNote script="Hebrew" scope="major"/>
						</handDesc>
						<additions>
							<p>Appended to the manuscript are the following fragments, originally portions of other manuscripts: folios 195r, 204v - Azharot of <name type="person" role="author">Solomon ibn Gabirol</name>, followed by a series of hosh῾anot; folios 205r-211r - Keter malkhut of <name type="person" role="author">Solomon ibn Gabirol</name>; folios 211v-212v - two poetical pieces; folio 213 - a calendar leaf on the years <date calendar="Hebrew">5492</date>-<date calendar="Hebrew">5505</date> (<date calendar="Gregorian">1732</date>-<date calendar="Gregorian">1745</date>). The first three parts belong most probably to the 17th century.</p>
							<p>Folios 44-45, which originally belonged to another manuscript, are now bound with the present manuscript just before shaḥarit of Rosh ha-Shanah. This fragment is also of 17th century. Folio 44r has a note, in a fading ink, of a viduy after the passing of Rabi Yehudah Zeruvavel.</p>
							<p>Folio 1r: a note of a former owner, <name type="person" role="owner">Yosef Ben Shalom ben Yesha῾</name>, written over an erasure originally occupied by another name.</p>
						</additions>
